title: Ask HN: ChatGPT is down, and now, so am I. Same?
text:
For the past ten minutes, I'm seeing: "ChatGPT is at capacity right now. We're experiencing exceptionally high demand. Please hang tight as we work on scaling our systems."

Does anyone else feel.... suddenly more lonely?

And if so, what does this suggest about how we will relate to AI assistants? I'm low-key horrifed that a bunch of math in a datacenter has, over the course of a week, manipulated my sense of reality to the point that, in my mammalian pack-animal gut, I miss it like a person, even if its absence is brief.

We have created the most powerful influencer of all time, at a moment of great political peril, and I'm shaken.
